description:
It’s time for our annual “What’s New in Mobile” talks night! Google I/O and WWDC have been and gone, so for our June event we’ll get together and talk about all the exciting announcements!

* Jack Newcombe: What's New in iOS
* Scott Alexander-Bown: What's New from Google I/O
* David Branton: Digital Wellbeing - Notes from Google I/O

This time, we’ll be trying a new venue – the folks at Zone Digital will kindly be hosting us. Meetup.com was having some difficulty showing the correct location, but it’s just off the Old Market roundabout in Bristol, not far from Desklodge. BS2 0EQ.

- Doors will open at 6:30pm
- Food and drink will be available.
- Talks will start at 7pm.

After the event, we'll move on to a pub to continue the discussions. 🍷
title: What’s New in Mobile
